+## Result Summary
+
+- `@pgg/dashboard` production build passes consistently, but Vite reports a chunk warning because the single JS bundle is 2,006.87kB raw / 640.18kB gzip.
+- The large JS bundle is the main performance risk introduced by the MUI chart adoption path. `@mui/x-charts` and its d3 transitive dependencies are likely contributors, and route/component code splitting should be the next optimization candidate.
+- CSS remains small at 15.39kB raw / 2.55kB gzip, so the dark navy/cyan visual skin itself is not the dominant artifact-size cost.
+- Chart dimensions are stable in source: backlog bar chart uses a fixed 178px height and sprint donut uses a 120x120 fixed container, reducing layout shift risk.
+- Static fallback data remains large at 1,693,554 bytes raw / 313,776 bytes gzip. This was not introduced by the visual reskin, but QA should keep it as residual initial-load risk for static fallback mode.
+- Because verification mode is manual, browser interaction latency and React render count remain deferred to manual QA rather than invented numeric results.
